heaviest_rainfall.status: Today ranked 7th for the heaviest total rainfall during a storm, dropping a total of 23.86mm of rain over the storm duration of 31.0 hours with a maximum rate of 8.3mm per hour.  Record-breaking rain fell on 09 November 2025 with a total accumulation of 47.89mm over 144.8 hours and falling at a rate of 24.6mm per hour at times.

heaviest_rainrate.status: The rain rate reached 27.6mm per hour during the storm today (ranking 2nd from our records) and resulted in 6.1mm of total rain in 2.6 hours.  34.3mm per hour is the maximum rain rate ever recorded on 02 September 2025, during a 15.0 hour storm which dumped 21.19mm of rain from the clouds.

longest_rain.status: Rain fell for 31.0 hours on 09 November 2025 (ranking 7th from our records for the longest storm) and it produced a total of 23.86mm of rain at a maximum intensity of 8.3mm per hour.  On 09 November 2025, the rain lasted for 144.8 hours, which is the longest time recorded by our database.  47.89mm accumulated and it fell at 24.6mm per hour at times.
